      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 836: retryRequestOnNoAnswer() holds info-\u003emutex_ while calling dht()-\u003eputEncrypted() and arming the next async_wait(). If putEncrypted() invokes callbacks synchronously, re-enters connection-manager code, or takes a non-trivial amount of time, this can block peer-response handling and cancellation on the same ConnectionInfo. Keep the lock only long enough to inspect/update ConnectionInfo state, then perform DHT I/O and timer scheduling after releasing it. Suggested shape:\n```suggestion\n    bool scheduleNext \u003d false;\n    {\n        std::lock_guard lk(info-\u003emutex_);\n        if (!info-\u003ewaitingForPeerResponse_ || info-\u003eresponseReceived_ || !info-\u003eonConnected_)\n            return;\n        ++info-\u003eanswerRetries_;\n        scheduleNext \u003d info-\u003eanswerRetries_ \u003c DHT_MSG_MAX_RETRIES \u0026\u0026 info-\u003eanswerRetryTimer_;\n    }\n\n    // Do not hold info-\u003emutex_ while issuing DHT operations.\n    dht()-\u003eputEncrypted(key, devicePk, value, ...);\n\n    if (scheduleNext) {\n        info-\u003eanswerRetryTimer_-\u003eexpires_after(DHT_MSG_RETRY_INTERVAL);\n        info-\u003eanswerRetryTimer_-\u003easync_wait(...);\n    }\n```",
